@node Manual installation
@section Manual installation

Clone the repository and add its location to your load path:

@lisp
(add-to-list 'load-path "path/to/kelly")
(require 'kelly)
@end lisp

Replace @samp{"path/to/kelly"} with the actual path to your local clone.

@node Package managers
@section Package managers

With any of the common package managers, add the appropriate form to your init file:

@lisp
;; with vc (Emacs 30 or later)
(use-package kelly
  :vc (:url "https://github.com/benthamite/kelly"))

;; with elpaca
(use-package kelly
  :ensure (:host github :repo "benthamite/kelly"))

;; with straight
(use-package kelly
  :straight (:host github :repo "benthamite/kelly"))

;; with quelpa
(use-package kelly
  :quelpa (kelly :fetcher github :repo "benthamite/kelly"))
@end lisp

@node Requirements
@chapter Requirements

@samp{kelly.el} requires Emacs 25.1 or later.  It has no external dependencies.

@node User options
@chapter User options

All user options belong to the @code{kelly} customization group and can be configured interactively via @samp{M-x customize-group RET kelly RET} or by setting them in your init file.

