@end menu

@node Core calculation
@section Core calculation

@findex kelly-calculate
The function @code{kelly-calculate} takes two arguments: a win probability @emph{p} (a number between 0 and 1) and net fractional odds @emph{b} (a positive number).  It returns the Kelly fraction scaled by @code{kelly-fraction} (@ref{Fractional Kelly}).

The underlying formula is:

@example
f = ((b + 1) * p - 1) / b
@end example

The function validates its inputs: it signals an error if @emph{b} is zero (which would cause division by zero) or if @code{kelly-fraction} is not a positive number.

@lisp
;; 60% win probability, 2:1 fractional odds, full Kelly
(let ((kelly-fraction 1))
  (kelly-calculate 0.6 2))  ; => 0.4
@end lisp

@node Expected value and wager sizing
@section Expected value and wager sizing

@findex kelly-get-expectation
@findex kelly-get-wager-amount
The function @code{kelly-get-expectation} computes the expected net profit per unit wagered, given a win probability @emph{p} and net odds @emph{b}.  The formula is @samp{p * b - (1 - p)}.  A positive return value indicates a bet with positive expected value.

The function @code{kelly-get-wager-amount} multiplies the Kelly fraction by the bankroll to produce the absolute wager amount.

@node Bankroll management
@section Bankroll management

@findex kelly-get-bankroll
@findex kelly-read-bankroll
The function @code{kelly-get-bankroll} returns the current value of @code{kelly-bankroll} (@ref{Bankroll}).  If @code{kelly-bankroll} is @code{nil}, it prompts the user via @code{kelly-read-bankroll} and stores the result.

The function @code{kelly-read-bankroll} prompts interactively for a positive bankroll amount without modifying any global variable.  It can be called directly if you want to update the bankroll mid-session:

@lisp
(setq kelly-bankroll (kelly-read-bankroll))
@end lisp

@node Odds conversion
@section Odds conversion

@findex kelly-read-fractional-odds
@findex kelly-read-decimal-odds
@findex kelly-read-moneyline-odds
@findex kelly-read-implied-probability
@findex kelly-read-implied-percent
Each odds format has a dedicated reader function that prompts the user for input and returns the equivalent fractional odds value.  These are:

@itemize
@item
@code{kelly-read-fractional-odds} --- Reads fractional odds directly (must be positive).
@item
@code{kelly-read-decimal-odds} --- Reads decimal odds (must be greater than 1) and subtracts 1 to convert to fractional.
@item
@code{kelly-read-moneyline-odds} --- Reads moneyline odds (any non-zero number) and converts to fractional.
@item
@code{kelly-read-implied-probability} --- Reads a probability between 0 and 1 exclusive and converts to fractional odds via @samp{(1 - p) / p}.
@item
@code{kelly-read-implied-percent} --- Reads a percentage between 0 and 100 exclusive and converts to fractional odds via @samp{(100 - pct) / pct}.
@end itemize

All reader functions validate their input in a loop, re-prompting if the entered value is out of range.  The appropriate reader is selected automatically by @code{kelly-read-b} based on the value of @code{kelly-b-parameter-format} (@ref{Odds format}).

